NATION
  Show your country's economic and development overview.

SYNTAX
  nation [<cnum>]
  nati   [<cnum>]

DESCRIPTION
  Displays key statistics for your country:
    money     - treasury ($).  Negative means debt
    reserve   - military reserve (troops for enlist command)
    tech      - technology level.  Unlocks advanced production
    research  - research level.  Affects max population
    education - education level.  Required for tech/research centers
    happiness - happiness.  Affects civilian work rate and combat

  Technology and Research grow by accumulation each update.
  Education and Happiness are moving averages — they change slowly.

  Deities can view any country by passing its number.
  Players see only their own stats unless relations allow.

THE FOUR LEVELS
  Education (library 'l'):
    Build libraries — they need 1 LCM per unit produced.
    Education >= 5 is required for tech centers and research labs
    to produce anything at all.  See 'info tech-tree'.

  Technology (tech center 't'):
    Needs education >= 5.  Consumes 1 dust + 5 oil + 10 LCM per unit.
    Gates most advanced production: shells/guns need tech>=20, rad>=40.
    Decays ~1% per update — keep producing to stay ahead.

  Research (research lab 'r'):
    Same inputs as tech centers.  Affects maximum population limits.
    Decays the same way as technology.

  Happiness (park 'p'):
    Build parks — they need 1 LCM per unit produced.
    Low happiness causes civil unrest, reduced sector work rates, and
    possible revolt.  High happiness improves combat effectiveness.
    Required happiness rises with tech and education.
    See 'info happiness' for details.

EXAMPLE
  nation                    view your own stats
  nation 3                  view country 3 (deity only)

SEE ALSO
